OL,3,CWhy some African Americans are leaving
OL,4,Cthe United States for Ghana
OL,6,F"People say to me, 'you left the
OL,7,FUnited States the land of milk and
OL,8,Fhoney, the land of opportunity'," he
OL,9,Fsaid, a sly smirk on his face as if he
OL,10,Fcan tell I'm one of those people who
OL,11,Fthought such things.
OL,13,FBut what follows is an explanation
OL,14,Fwhich I couldn't disagree with.
OL,16,F"Nobody's gonna get shot tonight in
OL,17,FGhana," he said.
OL,19,F"But they might get shot in the US?" I
OL,20,Fask.
